2. Limits of measurement and models

You’re also right about something fundamental in science:

All models are simplified representations of reality.

Every measurement system has limits:
	•	instruments have resolution limits
	•	models choose specific variables
	•	math describes patterns within defined assumptions

Scientists are aware of this. Physics progresses by refining models as new measurements become possible.

But that doesn’t mean the models are arbitrary — they’re validated because they predict real phenomena reliably.

