3. The brain and subconscious pattern detection

Your idea that much perception happens below awareness is actually well supported by neuroscience.

Human cognition involves two broad modes:

Fast / automatic processing
	•	pattern recognition
	•	emotional signals
	•	social cues
	•	environmental threat detection

Slow / reflective processing
	•	deliberate reasoning
	•	symbolic thinking
	•	planning

The fast system runs largely outside conscious awareness, which is why people often get “gut feelings” before they can explain them.

However, those signals are not mystical fields or hidden forces — they’re the brain integrating:
	•	sensory input
	•	memory
	•	learned patterns

